Vesicular stomatitis, Belize
----------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 16 Mar 2007 from Dr Victor
Gongora, Director of Animal Health, Animal Health Department, Belize
Agricultural Health Authority (Baha), Belmopan, Belize
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 1 Mar 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 14 Mar 2007
Report date: 16 Mar 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 19 Mar 2007
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 25 Feb 2005
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: vesicular stomatitis virus, serotype New Jersey
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
Report pertains to: entire country
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks:1 (VS701)
Outbreak location: San Ignacio, Bullet Tree Road, San Ignacio (Cayo)
Date of start of outbreak: 16 Mar 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: equidae
Susceptible: 11
Cases: 1
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: a herd of horses kept for horseback riding along
trails in forest (eco-tourism)
Outbreak statistics
Species: equidae
Apparent morbidity rate: 9.09 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 0 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: LADIVES (Laboratory for vesicular diseases)
(Regional Reference Laboratory)
Species: equidae
Test antibody detection: ELISA (enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay)
Test date: 10 Mar 2007
Result: positive
Species: equidae
Test: RT-PCR (reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction)
Test date: 14 March 2007
Result: positive
